title: Supported Double Height Terraces - means open terraces, unenclosed on at-least one side with railing and lying wholly within building line with supports underneath and having minimum height of two floors
clause_text: Supported Double Height Terraces - means open terraces, unenclosed on at-least one side with railing and lying wholly within building line with supports underneath and having minimum height of two floors. Tenement - means an independent dwelling unit with a kitchen or cooking alcove.
